.
YouTube API Services
We use the
YouTube API Services
to offer certain features, such as displaying and responding to comments on the user’s own YouTube videos, as well as analyzing data related to YouTube channels. To provide these features, the user must grant the necessary access permissions. The user must authenticate with YouTube, and we receive a token that allows us to access the API. By using this tool, the user agrees that their access and use are subject to the YouTube Terms of Service (
https://www.youtube.com/t/terms
). Additionally, the user accepts the Google Privacy Policy (
http://www.google.com/policies/privacy
).
The collected data is used to provide the functionalities of this tool, particularly for managing and responding to comments, as well as for analyzing and evaluating the reach and performance of the user’s YouTube channels and videos. The user’s data will
not
be shared with third parties, unless it is necessary to provide the service (for example, by involving service providers).
The user can revoke the granted permission at any time via the Google Security Page (
https://security.google.com/settings/security/permissions
). Additionally, the user can contact our customer service for questions regarding data deletion or storage.
Processed data: Content data (comments and replies from own videos, including text, name, and image link of the author). Data related to the user’s YouTube channels (e.g., reach and performance of a channel or individual videos, viewing time, other statistics, and analyses provided by YouTube).
